by The KL-22 » Tue Dec 17, 2019 10:14 pm

Terra Britania wrote:They speak a language which is basically Catalan with a splash of English. There are a handful of Cantelese language excerpts available, and I recognised Banara Kingal and Aus Nobile that are, correct me if I'm wrong, from English (the non-French, non-Latin parts of it), being from King and House, respectively. The Aristocracy also spoke English, or at least some sort of dialect of English, before this Cantelo English became extinct in the 1700s.

I am going to hazard a guess that the language spoken in the factbooks would be Anglish, a variant of English developed in modern times removing all possible non-Germanic influences, which is a fascinating project to read up on. Aside from that, the royal family seems to be essentially the same as that which exists in our universe, so I would hazard a guess that this is the result of a war which occurred with France rather than Germany for World War 1, given the presence of an independent Brittany, a Greater Belgium and Italy, and Germany in its prewar borders. Interesting to think about, really.

EDIT: Reading more, there's also the matter of the Norman line of English Kings breaking off with William II, but I'm not sure what other historical portents that'd bring had it happened.

The Servants reject technology in favour of what they refer to as the Will, which is essentially the power to warp reality itself out of pure belief. This power relies heavily upon the user's conviction, and therefore can't be used without absolute, genuine faith. The Will is divided into three subsets, known as Potential, Control, and Intention, each of which is associated with a specific test that adherents of the Will must go through.

Inkopolia is ruled by a semi-absolute theocratic monarchy centred around the Woomy, the alleged creator-goddess and ancient ruler of the Inkling species, with matrilineal succession. The Inkling religion presumably involves some degree of reincarnation, as the Empress is believed to have personally known the Woomy in other lives. Matriarchy is a recurring theme throughout their government, not just regarding the Empress' succession but also in their legislature and the Empress' advisory council - the latter is explicitly required to be all-female, while the former is referred to as the House of Dames.
